// STATIC SPAWN DATA //	Other				// NUMCONFIG   NBRmini NBRmaxi     AREA-RADIUS  COORDX	 COORDY 	COORDZ	FloorNumb FloorHeight	Spawned		SpawnDist	ChoseZconfiguration		NumOfCHEST	CHESTcoordX		CHESTcoordY		CHESTcoordZ		ReactivationDelay	SpawningOptions//

/// If you want to add personal static hordes, you have to modify a line above

/// if you want to deactivate static spawns properly (and save server ressources) put 0 in first column (NUMCONFIG), for exemple :
/// ref autoptr TFloatArray data_HordeStatic282 = {	0,		5,		8,				40,		7245,		0,		3025,		0,		0,			0,			100,		101,						0,			0,				0,				0,				0,				100 };// => correctly disabled

// ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/// NUMCONFIG 	: 0 => to deactivate the spawn / to activate it => enter the number corresponding of the XXX of the data_HordeStaticXXX

/// NBRmini		: Minimum number of Z to spawn (!! this number will be multiply by the ratio "4" of the RealTimeTweaks.json file (if "4" = 50 => quantity spawned will be 50%, so you need double the quantities)
/// NBRmaxi		: Maximum number of Z to spawn (!! this number will be multiply by the ratio "4" of the RealTimeTweaks.json file (if "4" = 50 => quantity spawned will be 50%, so you need double the quantities)

/// AREA-RADIUS	: The radius of the spawn area

/// COORDX		: X coordinate of the spawn
/// COORDZ		: Z coordinate of the spawn

/// COORDY		: Y coordinate of the spawn. 
/// If you don't need to populate a building, let this coordinate to 0. 
/// If you want to populate a building, you have to find its Y coordinate (using Community Online tool or other tool like that) 
/// If you want to prevent zeds spawning in wall, use a negative value (same value but negative) 
/// Be aware that negative value delete most of the zeds spawning outside the building too (so it impacts real number of zombies spawning compared to theoric NBRmini/NBRmaxi).

/// FloorNumb	: Number of floors if you need to populate a building
/// FloorHeight	: Height of the building floors

/// Spawned		: !!! Don't modify !!! (default : 0)

/// SpawnDist			: Distance to which the group spawns
/// ChoseZconfiguration : Choose the type of zombie to spawn (see ZombiesChooseCategories.c file and look for the number in variable name. For exemple variable name data_Horde_102_CastelCategories, 102 is the number to spawn Castle zeds categorie)

/// NumOfCHEST	: Choose the type of Chest to spawn. 0 => no chest (see ChestLoot.c file and look for the number in variable name. For example variable name data_Chest002, 2 is the number to spawn the second chest)
/// CHESTcoordX	: X coord of the chest (if 0 the coordinates of the spawn (COORDX/COORDY/COORDZ)replace the chest coordinate)
/// CHESTcoordY	: Y coord of the chest 
/// CHESTcoordZ	: Z coord of the chest 

/// ReactivationDelay : Apply a delay (in minutes) before the horde can spawn again (to avoid players looting again and again the same place if there is loot chest)
/// If you set a negative value it will choose a value between 10 min a the absolute value you set (for example : -30 => random between 10 and 30 minutes)

/// SpawningOptions : 
/// 	- 100: default value
///		- 200: if zombies are not spawning (the spawn location may be outside the navmesh)
///		- If zombies are spawning under the building try to use a negative value in this column (same value but negative)